availability_zone.description: The name of the Availability Zone (AZ) where the odb network is located. Changing this will force terraform to create new resource

availability_zone_id.description: The AZ ID of the AZ where the ODB network is located. Changing this will force terraform to create new resource.

backup_subnet_cidr.description: The CIDR range of the backup subnet for the ODB network. Changing this will force terraform to create new resource. Constraints: - Must not overlap with the CIDR range of the client subnet. - Must not overlap with the CIDR ranges of the VPCs that are connected to the ODB network. - Must not use the following CIDR ranges that are reserved by OCI: - 100.106.0.0/16 and 100.107.0.0/16 - 169.254.0.0/16 - 224.0.0.0 - 239.255.255.255 - 240.0.0.0 - 255.255.255.255

client_subnet_cidr.description: The CIDR notation for the network resource. Changing this will force terraform to create new resource. Constraints: - Must not overlap with the CIDR range of the backup subnet. - Must not overlap with the CIDR ranges of the VPCs that are connected to the ODB network. - Must not use the following CIDR ranges that are reserved by OCI: - 100.106.0.0/16 and 100.107.0.0/16 - 169.254.0.0/16 - 224.0.0.0 - 239.255.255.255 - 240.0.0.0 - 255.255.255.255

created_at.description: The date and time when the ODB network was created.

custom_domain_name.description: The name of the custom domain that the network is located. custom_domain_name and default_dns_prefix both can't be given.

default_dns_prefix.description: The default DNS prefix for the network resource. Changing this will force terraform to create new resource.

delete_associated_resources.description: If set to true deletes associated OCI resources. Default false.

display_name.description: The user-friendly name for the odb network. Changing this will force terraform to create a new resource.

managed_services.description: The managed services configuration for the ODB network.

oci_dns_forwarding_configs.description: The DNS resolver endpoint in OCI for forwarding DNS queries for the ociPrivateZone domain.

oci_network_anchor_id.description: The unique identifier of the OCI network anchor for the ODB network.

oci_network_anchor_url.description: The URL of the OCI network anchor for the ODB network.

oci_resource_anchor_name.description: The name of the OCI resource anchor for the ODB network.

oci_vcn_id.description: The unique identifier  Oracle Cloud ID (OCID) of the OCI VCN for the ODB network.

oci_vcn_url.description: The URL of the OCI VCN for the ODB network.

peered_cidrs.description: The list of CIDR ranges from the peered VPC that are allowed access to the ODB network. Please refer odb network peering documentation.

percent_progress.description: The amount of progress made on the current operation on the ODB network, expressed as a percentage.

region.description: Region where this resource will be [managed](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/rande.html#regional-endpoints). Defaults to the Region set in the [provider configuration](https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/aws/latest/docs#aws-configuration-reference).

s3_access.description: Specifies the configuration for Amazon S3 access from the ODB network.

s3_policy_document.description: Specifies the endpoint policy for Amazon S3 access from the ODB network.

status.description: The status of the network resource.

status_reason.description: Additional information about the current status of the ODB network.

zero_etl_access.description: Specifies the configuration for Zero-ETL access from the ODB network.

create.description: A string that can be [parsed as a duration](https://pkg.go.dev/time#ParseDuration) consisting of numbers and unit suffixes, such as "30s" or "2h45m". Valid time units are "s" (seconds), "m" (minutes), "h" (hours).

delete.description: A string that can be [parsed as a duration](https://pkg.go.dev/time#ParseDuration) consisting of numbers and unit suffixes, such as "30s" or "2h45m". Valid time units are "s" (seconds), "m" (minutes), "h" (hours). Setting a timeout for a Delete operation is only applicable if changes are saved into state before the destroy operation occurs.

update.description: A string that can be [parsed as a duration](https://pkg.go.dev/time#ParseDuration) consisting of numbers and unit suffixes, such as "30s" or "2h45m". Valid time units are "s" (seconds), "m" (minutes), "h" (hours).
